The paper discusses the use of crowdsourced information to improve the user experience of mobile apps, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the generation of feedback to help developers deal with potential errors, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of crowdsourcing to gather information about apps, devices, and users could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the App Store 2.0 vision, which could relate to cybersecurity (cs.CY) in terms of ensuring the security of the app store and the apps available on it.
